The paper focuses on process modeling and understanding using sensor-based detection and deep learning techniques. This falls under the scope of computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves extracting spatio-temporal features from sensory inputs. The use of deep learning structures for modeling and estimation suggests that the paper could also be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The application of the system in human-computer interfaces and automation systems suggests a potential fit for human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the use of Gaussian mixture models for process completeness estimation suggests a potential fit for information retrieval (cs.IR).
